What really excites me is the possibility of collaborative meaning-making. I'd want the audience to become co-creators, piecing together fragments and filling gaps with their own interpretation. There's something beautiful about art that only becomes complete through the act of experiencing it, where each person's engagement creates a slightly different work entirely."}

